description: From the Late Latin orbiculāris, from Latin orbiculus, diminutive of orbis (“orb”).

adjectives.description: orbicular (comparative more orbicular, superlative most orbicular)

entries.meaning: Circular or spherical in shape; round.
examples: […]  the Method used by Sailors when they mutiny, by signing their names in an orbicular manner, which they call a round Robin;  […]
